te." Even if the deal is done, Sears would still need significant cash to operate because of challenges in retail, the ratings agency said.In recent decades, Sears, which was the world's largest retailer in the 1960s, has struggled in the face of declining foot traffic at its brick-and-mortar stores.In another attempt to avoid bankruptcy, money-losing Sears last year sold its Craftsman tool brand to power tool maker Stanley BlackDecker  for $900 million.This article appears in:World Markets,StocksReferenced Symbols:AMZN,
