 payments service in India.The company also plans to oppose new legislation in India that would require it to store user data in the country.Separately, WhatsApp is looking for an India head too.It last month appointed a grievance officer for Indian users based out of its headquarters in Menlo Park, California, like other global tech firms whose grievance officers sit outside of India.India has, however, said it will toughen up its tech laws including pushing U.S. tech giants to have their grievance officers in India.This article appears in:Stocks,PoliticsReferenced Symbols:FB,
